subSubSection.paragraph:
Chelymorpha reimoseri
makes complex ootheca (
Figs. 1–2
). The female deposits from
30 to 110
eggs in each ootheca. Preserved in alcohol ootheca is yellow and in its structure resembles honeycomb (
Figs 1, 2
). Eggs are elongate-oval (
Fig. 27
), preserved in alcohol are uniformly yellowish-white. Surface of the chorion is smooth without punctation or any distinct sculpture (
Fig. 28
).

Six stemmata on each side of head (
Fig. 34
).

