subSubSection.paragraph:
Frontal surface of head with four small, vertical, pointed setae (
V 1–4
), and five frontal rows of club-like setae: row Fa with three setae, Fb with five (sometimes six) setae, Fc with three setae, Fd with single seta, Fe with two setae and one campaniform sensillum between setae Fc 1 and Fe 1 (
Fig. 11
). Temporal surface of head with three setae slightly shorter and pointed than setae of frons (T 1–3 ) and campaniform sensillum (
Fig. 12
).

Antennae two-segmented, set in membranous ring (
Figs 36, 37
). Both segments stout, more or less as long as wide. First antennomere with four campaniform sensilla, second with one small seta at base, and with a group of 6 peg-like sensilla at the apex: one prominent (sensory appendix) and five smaller.

